State MSM Profile: Nevada

Background & Methods

In 2015-2016, researchers at Emory University partnered with colleagues at the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) to develop methods to estimate the number of men who have sex with men (MSM) residing in each county in the United States. Using population and housing data from the American Community Survey and estimates from two peer-reviewed publications (Oster et al., 2015 & Purcell et al., 2012), they derived an indirect estimate of MSM population sizes that took into account both the urbanicity of the county as well as its density of households with a male householder and a male same-sex partner.

The full methodology is published in the Journal of Medical Internet Research - Public Health and Surveillance:

Grey JA, Bernstein KT, Sullivan PS, Purcell DW, Chesson HW, Gift TL, Rosenberg ES. Estimating the population sizes of men who have sex with men in US states and counties using data from the American Community Survey. JMIR Public Health Surveill 2016;2(1):e14. DOI: 10.2196/publichealth.5365

Overview of MSM in Nevada

An estimated 51,725 men who have sex with men (MSM) resided in Nevada in 2013, representing 1.1% of the 4,503,084 MSM in the United States. Of the 1,038,437 adult men of Nevada, 5.0% had had sex with another man in the past 5 years, which was greater than the overall percentage of adult men in the United States who were MSM (3.9%).

Most MSM in Nevada resided in central counties of large metropolitan areas (90.0%). Including both central and fringe counties, 90.0% resided in a large metropolitan area.


Percentage of MSM by urbanicity, United States and Nevada, 2013

MSM in Nevada Counties

Among counties or county-equivalent areas in Nevada, Clark County had the largest population of MSM at 46,529, representing 90.0% of all MSM in the state. Clark County also had the highest percentage of MSM among adult men in Nevada at 6.2%. This was greater than the percentage for Nevada as a whole, which was 5.0% of adult men.

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.



MSM in Nevada Metropolitan Statistical Areas

Las Vegas-Henderson-Paradise Metropolitan Statistical Area

The Las Vegas-Henderson-Paradise MSA had the largest metropolitan population of MSM in Nevada at 46,529, or 90.0% of all MSM in the state. Of the 744,929 adult men in Las Vegas-Henderson-Paradise, an estimated 6.2% were MSM.

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.




Reno Metropolitan Statistical Area

The Reno MSA had a population of 3,775 MSM, or 7.3% of all MSM in Nevada. Of the 165,359 adult men in Reno, an estimated 2.3% were MSM.

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.




Carson City Metropolitan Statistical Area

The Carson City MSA had a population of 276 MSM, or 0.5% of all MSM in Nevada. Of the 22,204 adult men in Carson City, an estimated 1.2% were MSM.

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.
